==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hurricane
<hw>Hur"ri*cane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>hurracan</ets>; orig. a Carib word signifying, a high wind.]</ety>
<def>A violent storm, characterized by extreme fury and sudden changes
of the wind, and generally accompanied by rain, thunder, and lightning;
-- especially prevalent in the East and West Indies. Also used
figuratively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like the smoke in a <qex>hurricane</qex> whirl'd.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Each guilty thought to me is⟦br⟧
A dreadful <qex>hurricane</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Massinger.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hurricane bird</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
frigate bird.</cd> -- <col><b>Hurricane deck</b></col>.
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <cd>See under <er>Deck</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hurricano</ent>⟦br⟧
